President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Republic of Chile to attend the Opening Ceremony of the 2023 Pan American Games on October 20, 2023 in Santiago. The delegation will be led by the Honorable Xavier Becerra, Secretary of the United States Department of Health and Human Services. Other members of the delegation include the Honorable Bernadette M. Meehan, U.S. Ambassador to the Republic of Chile, and Mrs. Chaunte Lowe OLY, a 4-Time Olympian, Medalist for Women's Track and Field, and Member of the President's Council on Sports, Fitness, and Nutrition.